Font Fallback and Weight Variations Test
    
    
        Primary Font - Liberation Sans
        
            This text uses Liberation Sans as the primary font family with Arial as fallback. The quick brown fox jumps over the lazy dog.
        
    
    
    
        Fallback Test - NonExistent → Liberation Sans
        
            This text requests a non-existent font first, then falls back to Liberation Sans. The rendering should be identical to the previous example.
        
    
    
    
        Font Weight Variations (Liberation Sans)
        Font Weight 100 (Thin) - May fallback to regular
        Font Weight 200 (Extra Light) - May fallback to regular
        Font Weight 300 (Light) - May fallback to regular
        Font Weight 400 (Regular) - Should display correctly
        Font Weight 500 (Medium) - May display as bold
        Font Weight 600 (Semi Bold) - May display as bold
        Font Weight 700 (Bold) - Should display correctly
        Font Weight 800 (Extra Bold) - May display as bold
        Font Weight 900 (Black) - May display as bold
    
    
    
        Mixed Font Stack - Roboto + Liberation Sans
        
            Roboto Regular: This text should display in Roboto with Liberation Sans as fallback.
        
        
            Roboto Bold: This text should display in bold Roboto with bold Liberation Sans as fallback.
        
    
    
    
        Font Style Variations
        Normal style text
        Italic style text - should use Liberation Sans Italic
        Oblique style text - may synthesize from regular
